Beginner Practice Scripts
Hello World

bash
Copy
Edit
echo "Hello DevOps"
Loop through a list from a file
servers.txt

nginx
Copy
Edit
server1
server2
server3
Script:

bash
Copy
Edit
while read server; do
    echo "Processing $server"
done < servers.txt
Check disk usage (alert if > 80%)

bash
Copy
Edit
usage=$(df / | grep / | awk '{print $5}' | sed 's/%//')
if [ "$usage" -gt 80 ]; then
    echo "Warning: Disk usage is ${usage}%!"
else
    echo "Disk usage is under control."
fi
Intermediate DevOps Scripts
Check if a service is running

bash
Copy
Edit
service="nginx"
if systemctl is-active --quiet "$service"; then
    echo "$service is running"
else
    echo "$service is NOT running"
fi
Backup a directory with timestamp

bash
Copy
Edit
src="/var/www/html"
dest="/backup/html_$(date +%F_%H-%M-%S).tar.gz"
tar -czf "$dest" "$src"
echo "Backup saved to $dest"
Deploy code to multiple servers (SSH loop)

bash
Copy
Edit
for server in $(cat servers.txt); do
    echo "Deploying to $server"
    ssh user@$server "cd /app && git pull origin main && systemctl restart app"
done
Advanced Practice Scripts
Monitor CPU and Memory Usage

bash
Copy
Edit
echo "CPU Load: $(uptime | awk '{print $(NF-2),$(NF-1),$NF}')"
echo "Memory Usage:"
free -h
Check website health

bash
Copy
Edit
url="https://example.com"
if curl -s --head "$url" | grep "200 OK" > /dev/null; then
    echo "$url is up"
else
    echo "$url is down"
fi
Automated log cleanup

bash
Copy
Edit
find /var/log -type f -name "*.log" -mtime +7 -exec rm -f {} \;
echo "Old logs deleted"
